This paper is primarily focused on the formal semantics of the POSIX shell, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). However, it also discusses the use of the shell for managing computer systems, which could fall under operating systems (cs.OS) or software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of formal methods for studying the shell, which could fall under logic in computer science (cs.LO) or formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
